Japan’s Bonds Rise as Shares Drop; 30-Year Yields Fall to 1.895%

-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 
2011-10-04T00:25:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/japan-s-bonds-rise-as-shares-drop-30-year-yields-fall-to-1-895-.html
Japan ’s bonds rose as domestic shares
extended a global slump, supporting demand for the relative
safety of government debt.  The yield on the 30-year security slid 2.5 basis points to
1.895 percent as of 9:24 a.m. in Tokyo  To contact the reporter on this story:
